  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager (Construction/ Engineering)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Metta Welfare Association</strong></p>\n<p><strong>About the Role</strong><br>\nWe are looking for an experienced <strong>Project Manager</strong> to oversee the planning, coordination, and execution of the <strong>Maitri School Project</strong>. You will ensure the project is completed on time, within budget, and meets all quality and compliance standards.</p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Define project scope, objectives, and deliverables.</li>\n  <li>Plan and manage project resources, timelines, and budgets.</li>\n  <li>Develop and monitor project schedules and payment forecasts.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with government agencies, consultants, contractors, and vendors.</li>\n  <li>Provide regular progress updates and reports to management.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with regulatory and organisational standards.</li>\n  <li>Support other projects as assigned by management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Architecture, Engineering, Business, or Project Management.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years of relevant project management experience.</li>\n  <li>Strong coordination and stakeholder management skills.</li>\n  <li>Able to multitask, work independently, and meet deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why Join Us</strong><br>\nBe part of a meaningful project that contributes to building an inclusive educational environment for children with special needs.</p>",
